  //String concatination
  //There are two ways of concatenating string in Java

  //Type 1:By + (String concatenation) operator
  //Type 2:By concat() method

  //Let's look at the first Type by + (String concatination) operator
  //Javs String Concatenation Operator (+) is use to add strings. Ex:
  class testStringConcat1{
    public static void main (String args []){
    String s = "Birth" + "day";
    System.out.println(s);
    // A piece of Java compiler tansforms the code above to this:
    String s = (new StringBuilder()).append("Birth").append("day").toString();
    
    //String concatination by using concat() method
    //The String concat () method concatenates the specified string to the end of current string. Here is the syntax:
    public String concat (String another)

    //Now lets see an examples
    class testStringConcat2{
      public static void main (String args []){
        string s1 = "Birth";
        string s2 = "day";
        string s3 = s1 concat (s2);
        System.out.print.ln(s3);
      }
    }
  }
}
